The Dennis Prager Radio Show OCT-21-2013 MON






Dennis Prager Radio Show



Prager 20131021  3 Not Noble Nobel

Prager H3: The Nobel Peace Prize was given to a UN Chemical Weapons inspection group
 that no one has ever heard of.

 The Prize, once so valued, is now a joke 

 In the Los Angeles, immigrant parents want their kids to learn English as quickly as possible,
 but the school district says no 

  This has been a very cool weather year in the United States.




Prager 20131021  2 Feeling Good

Prager H2: If you want to feel good, get a massage.

 If you want to do good, especially in politics, you need a plan and goal.

 Those who wanted to push the country beyond the debt ceiling to stop ObamaCare might feel good,

 but their actions have had a negative consequence for the Republican Party and its ability to win elections
